v 3
d 'COEFCONV': module to compute comprehensive marginal effects from regression coefficients
d
d  coefconv computes 26 marginal effect types for every predictor
d  in the most recently estimated regression model, organized
d  into 7 interpretation families: (1) raw and standardized
d  slopes (beta, beta*, X-standardized, Y-standardized);
d  (2) elasticity and semi-elasticities (point elasticity at
d  means, X-semi-elasticity, Y-semi-elasticity); (3) basis-point
d  and percentage-point effects; (4) relative and proportional
d  effects; (5) variance-importance measures including Pratt's
d  decomposition of R-squared; (6) discrete delta-Y effects from
d  moving X from its median to each quantile; and (7) discrete
d  change effects under growth-rate, IQR, full-range, SD, and
d  custom delta-X scenarios. All inputs are drawn live from
d  Stata's e() results and restricted to the estimation sample.
d  Zero-order correlations are computed automatically for the
d  Pratt decomposition.
d
d  Companion program coefconv_plot produces three named graphs:
d  a standardized-slope forest plot with Cohen (1988) benchmarks,
d  a Pratt R-squared bar chart identifying suppressor variables,
d  and a per-variable discrete-effects ladder chart showing
d  delta-Y in original Y units across nine realistic scenarios.
d
d  Compatible with regress, ivregress, areg, xtreg, and other
d  estimators that store e(b), e(V), e(depvar), and e(sample).
d
d KW: marginal effects
d KW: standardized coefficients
d KW: elasticity
d KW: semi-elasticity
d KW: Pratt importance
d KW: relative importance
d KW: discrete change
d KW: regression post-estimation
d KW: forest plot
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260404
d
d Author: Noman Arshed, Sunway Business School, Sunway University
d Support: email nouman.arshed@gmail.com
d
f coefconv.ado
f coefconv_plot.ado
f coefconv.sthlp
f coefconv_plot.sthlp
f coefconv_examples.do
e
